WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:11.378
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.698 --> 00:33.600
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:33.666 --> 00:34.968
- It was so cool of Jeremy

00:35.034 --> 00:36.236
to invite us to his lecture

00:36.302 --> 00:38.571
on active listening
and staying focused.

00:38.638 --> 00:40.306
- Ooh, what's that?

00:40.373 --> 00:42.041
- Piri?

00:42.108 --> 00:44.077
Uh...wait up!

00:44.144 --> 00:46.346
- Look, Harvey.
A hole.

00:46.413 --> 00:48.047
[wind blowing]

00:48.114 --> 00:50.550
- Wow, it's very symmetrical.

00:50.617 --> 00:52.185
- I wonder what would happen

00:52.252 --> 00:54.220
{\an1}if I put all my body weight
forward,

00:54.287 --> 00:56.556
and slowly started to fall.

00:56.623 --> 00:57.757
- Wait, Piri!

00:57.824 --> 01:00.760
[screams]
both: Whoa!

01:00.827 --> 01:02.529
[both grunt]

01:02.595 --> 01:04.596
- Ow, I landed on my keys.

01:04.664 --> 01:06.266
- Look over there.

01:06.332 --> 01:11.271
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11.337 --> 01:14.841
both:
A secret garden.

01:14.908 --> 01:17.177
Whoa.

01:17.243 --> 01:20.380
<i>[funky soft music]</i>

01:20.447 --> 01:26.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:27.253 --> 01:30.123
{\an1}- Wow.
It beautiful!

01:30.190 --> 01:32.759
Lilacs, tulips, daffodils.

01:32.826 --> 01:34.461
- You know lots about flowers.

01:34.527 --> 01:36.463
{\an1}- Just spring arrangements
mostly.

01:36.529 --> 01:40.667
{\an3}- For the first three months
of my life, my mom fed me soil.

01:40.733 --> 01:42.001
- You know what?

01:42.068 --> 01:44.971
I think this whole place
is alive.

01:45.038 --> 01:46.673
We should give it a name.

01:46.739 --> 01:48.074
- I'll divine it's name

01:48.141 --> 01:50.643
with an ancient
throat-singing ritual.

01:50.710 --> 01:53.646
[warbling]

01:53.713 --> 01:55.081
♪ ♪

01:55.148 --> 01:56.649
It's name is Gordon.

01:56.716 --> 01:58.151
- With some sprucing up,

01:58.218 --> 02:00.787
Gordon could be
the nicest spot in Littlebark.

02:00.854 --> 02:02.188
<i>[soft music]</i>

02:02.255 --> 02:04.224
- Look, gardening tools!

02:04.290 --> 02:05.792
Gordon wants us to help him!

02:05.859 --> 02:08.228
We heed your call, Gordon.

02:08.294 --> 02:10.163
Oh, gasp!
Oh, no.

02:10.229 --> 02:14.167
That flower looks so sad.

02:14.234 --> 02:16.369
{\an3}Harvey, it's not breathing!
What do we do?

02:16.436 --> 02:19.572
{\an1}- Oh, I think it just needs
a little sunlight.

02:19.639 --> 02:26.579
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:29.415 --> 02:31.551
{\an1}See?
He's feeling better already.

02:31.618 --> 02:33.786
{\an3}- It's funny.
I never realized

02:33.853 --> 02:35.855
how vibrant your aura is.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.057
{\an1}- Oh, really?
Well, thanks, Piri.

02:38.124 --> 02:40.393
{\an3}- [giggles]

02:40.460 --> 02:43.129
{\an1}- Come on.
Let's get this place cleaned up.

02:43.196 --> 02:46.132
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

02:46.199 --> 02:53.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:12.859 --> 03:13.960
Whoa!

03:14.027 --> 03:17.163
[both giggling]

03:18.831 --> 03:25.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:28.942 --> 03:30.577
What a difference!

03:30.643 --> 03:34.714
- I think Gordon is really happy
with all the work we've done.

03:34.781 --> 03:36.382
- We make a great team.

03:36.449 --> 03:37.951
- Today has been amazing.

03:38.017 --> 03:41.154
I had a lot of fun hanging out
just the two of us.

03:41.220 --> 03:43.323
{\an3}- And I got to use
my dad's good china.

03:43.389 --> 03:45.024
- To celebrate,
I wrote a song

03:45.091 --> 03:47.060
from the point of view
of Mother Gaia.

03:47.126 --> 03:48.328
[playing upbeat flute music]

03:48.394 --> 03:49.862
- I can't wait for everyone

03:49.929 --> 03:52.932
to see this place.

03:52.999 --> 03:54.334
- Everyone?

03:54.400 --> 03:56.903
{\an3}- Yeah, you know
how much the guys like gardens.

03:56.970 --> 03:58.004
It'll be great.

03:58.071 --> 03:59.472
I'll be right back!

03:59.539 --> 04:00.807
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

04:00.873 --> 04:04.811
- But I thought
this was our special place.

04:04.877 --> 04:06.946
Why do I feel so upset?

04:07.013 --> 04:09.382
I can't explain it in words,

04:09.449 --> 04:12.285
but maybe I can with a song.

04:12.352 --> 04:15.488
[soft music playing]

04:15.555 --> 04:22.295
♪ ♪

04:22.362 --> 04:26.099
♪ What do you call
what I feel? ♪

04:26.165 --> 04:29.068
♪ It makes me happy
and nervous ♪

04:29.135 --> 04:31.371
♪ And it's so unreal ♪

04:31.437 --> 04:33.906
♪ It's weird ♪

04:33.973 --> 04:36.142
♪ I'm weird ♪

04:36.209 --> 04:37.310
[sighs]

04:37.377 --> 04:40.847
♪ When it's just Harvey and I ♪

04:40.913 --> 04:43.816
♪ I never want it to end ♪

04:43.883 --> 04:46.386
♪ And I don't know why ♪

04:46.452 --> 04:48.454
♪ It's dumb ♪

04:48.521 --> 04:50.023
♪ I'm dumb ♪

04:50.089 --> 04:51.824
♪ ♪

04:51.891 --> 04:53.893
♪ I'm freaking out ♪

04:53.960 --> 04:56.262
♪ I'm getting sweaty ♪

04:56.329 --> 05:01.034
♪ I just might
throw up my spaghetti ♪

05:01.100 --> 05:03.369
♪ It's a special kind of feel ♪

05:03.436 --> 05:06.773
♪ That I can't explain ♪

05:06.839 --> 05:08.174
- Piri, where are you?

05:08.241 --> 05:09.909
- Wrap it up, wrap it up,
wrap it up.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.577
<i>[somber music]</i>

05:11.644 --> 05:13.513
[sighs]

05:13.579 --> 05:15.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:15.682 --> 05:18.284
- Allow me
to introduce you all to Gordon.

05:18.351 --> 05:19.952
- Oh, this is lovely.

05:20.019 --> 05:23.022
{\an3}Ooh, these'll make
great spring arrangements.

05:23.089 --> 05:25.024
- Ew, guys, slow down.

05:25.091 --> 05:26.859
I'm wearing my clompers.

05:26.926 --> 05:29.429
- Ah, welcome, everyone.

05:29.495 --> 05:30.797
Make yourselves at home.

05:30.863 --> 05:33.266
{\an1}- Hey, Piri,
look at this flower I found.

05:33.332 --> 05:35.568
- Oh, uh-huh.

05:35.635 --> 05:36.969
- Oh, man,
this'll go awesome in my...

05:37.036 --> 05:38.604
- Oh, your eyes moved over here,

05:38.671 --> 05:40.373
{\an3}but that's okay.
I'll follow.

05:40.440 --> 05:42.575
{\an1}- Tha--that's--that's great,
Foo.

05:42.642 --> 05:45.011
{\an3}Excuse me.
[chuckles weakly]

05:45.078 --> 05:46.312
Hey, Harvey?

05:46.379 --> 05:48.648
{\an1}Um, could I steal you
for a second?

05:48.715 --> 05:51.684
- You're not going anywhere.
I am killing it right now.

05:51.751 --> 05:53.686
{\an3}- Piri, you might wanna
come back in an hour.

05:53.753 --> 05:56.622
{\an3}This one's got
the resilience of a horse.

05:56.689 --> 05:59.192
[all laughing]
- Oh, yeah!

05:59.258 --> 06:00.626
- [sighs]

06:00.693 --> 06:02.595
- Here I go!
I'm in!

06:02.662 --> 06:04.931
- I wish everyone would go away

06:04.997 --> 06:07.567
and it was just me and Harvey.

06:07.633 --> 06:11.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:12.038 --> 06:13.506
- Whew, let's take five.

06:13.573 --> 06:14.807
My arms are tired.

06:14.874 --> 06:18.010
Oh, my.
These daisies are stunning.

06:19.445 --> 06:22.381
[groaning]

06:22.448 --> 06:25.585
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:25.651 --> 06:27.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:27.920 --> 06:30.723
{\an3}Gordon, why in the name of Gaia
would you do that?

06:30.790 --> 06:33.092
{\an3}It's not nice
to throw people around like...

06:33.159 --> 06:34.527
[muffled speech]

06:34.594 --> 06:37.663
{\an1}- No, no, no, no.
Do not eat these plants.

06:37.730 --> 06:39.098
{\an3}- Oh.

06:39.165 --> 06:41.367
I think I understand.

06:43.169 --> 06:45.271
- Hey, anybody seen Dade?

06:45.338 --> 06:48.608
{\an3}- Uh, maybe he went
to take a nap.

06:48.674 --> 06:51.177
{\an3}- Well, that's weird.
Dade already had his nap today.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.412
{\an1}- Ah!
I need help!

06:53.479 --> 06:55.214
- Princess, what's wrong?

06:55.281 --> 06:56.549
- Ha, I lied.

06:56.616 --> 06:58.584
I just wanted you to look at me.

06:58.651 --> 06:59.485
[laughs]

06:59.552 --> 07:00.887
Watch me jump.

07:00.953 --> 07:02.121
[laughs]

07:02.188 --> 07:04.123
[muffled grunts]

07:04.190 --> 07:06.425
[screaming, fire blazing]

07:06.492 --> 07:08.461
[explosion]

07:08.528 --> 07:11.197
- Oh, how awful.

07:11.264 --> 07:13.666
{\an3}Fee, Foo, you two should
go check on her.

07:13.733 --> 07:15.434
- Nah, I don't feel like it.

07:15.501 --> 07:17.737
- She's fine.

07:17.804 --> 07:19.005
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:19.071 --> 07:21.140
- Huh?
[both scream]

07:21.207 --> 07:22.475
- Oh, my gosh!

07:22.542 --> 07:24.744
- What're you feeding
these plants?

07:24.811 --> 07:26.379
- Whee!

07:26.445 --> 07:28.581
It's trying to murder me!

07:28.648 --> 07:30.283
- Gordon, what're you doing?

07:30.349 --> 07:31.684
{\an3}- It's okay, Harvey.
[laughs weakly]

07:31.751 --> 07:33.252
He's just playing with them.

07:33.319 --> 07:36.656
{\an3}Hey, let's go have
another tea party picnic.

07:36.722 --> 07:38.658
- Oof.
- [grunts]

07:38.724 --> 07:40.026
both: Whoa!
- Ha--

07:40.092 --> 07:41.194
- Bye, guys!

07:41.260 --> 07:42.895
- Fee, Foo!

07:42.962 --> 07:49.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:53.239 --> 07:55.308
- Um, this isn't so bad, right?

07:55.374 --> 07:57.343
- We're in grave danger, Piri!

07:57.410 --> 07:59.145
Oh, no sugar, please.

07:59.212 --> 08:00.546
{\an3}[slurps]

08:00.613 --> 08:02.648
I think Gordon has gone crazy.

08:02.715 --> 08:04.584
We gotta find a way to escape.

08:04.650 --> 08:07.453
{\an1}- Or we could just spend
some quality time together.

08:07.520 --> 08:08.721
Oh, I know.

08:08.788 --> 08:10.289
{\an1}Let's share
what our favorite color is.

08:10.356 --> 08:12.325
Mine is innocent baby laughter.

08:12.391 --> 08:14.026
- Okay, here's my plan.

08:14.093 --> 08:16.495
{\an3}I'll distract Gordon with
some playful knock-knock jokes,

08:16.562 --> 08:18.431
{\an3}and then we'll
make a run for it.

08:18.497 --> 08:19.932
{\an3}Ready?
Hey, Gordon.

08:19.999 --> 08:21.801
{\an3}What do you call cheese
that isn't yours?

08:21.868 --> 08:24.003
{\an3}Nacho cheese!
Okay, go!

08:24.070 --> 08:25.872
{\an3}Whoa!
[grunts]

08:25.938 --> 08:27.573
{\an3}[squeaks]

08:27.640 --> 08:28.941
- Huh?
Wait!

08:29.008 --> 08:30.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:30.109 --> 08:31.143
[both grunt]

08:31.210 --> 08:33.312
[straining]

08:33.379 --> 08:34.813
- Why is this happening?

08:34.881 --> 08:36.883
- Okay, Gordon, that's enough.

08:36.948 --> 08:39.284
{\an1}Stop.

08:39.352 --> 08:41.020
- Hey, he listened to you.

08:41.087 --> 08:43.688
{\an1}- Um, Gordon isn't trying
to hurt us.

08:43.756 --> 08:46.726
I may have improvised a song

08:46.792 --> 08:48.761
about some of my feelings

08:48.828 --> 08:50.863
and Gordon thinks he's helping.

08:50.930 --> 08:53.032
{\an3}- What do you mean?
What feelings?

08:53.099 --> 08:56.636
{\an1}- Uh, I--I just
feel different around you.

08:56.702 --> 08:58.804
Like, butterflies in my stomach?

08:58.871 --> 09:00.239
Or a tapeworm.

09:00.306 --> 09:03.809
{\an1}I kind of told Gordon that
I wanted to spend time with you

09:03.876 --> 09:04.977
{\an1}alone.

09:05.044 --> 09:07.046
{\an3}- Oh...

09:07.113 --> 09:09.081
{\an1}- But he didn't mean
for all this to happen.

09:09.148 --> 09:11.284
Oh, I'm so embarrassed.

09:11.350 --> 09:12.285
{\an1}[sighs]

09:12.351 --> 09:14.520
[soft upbeat music playing]

09:14.587 --> 09:17.823
♪ He knows what I feel inside ♪

09:17.890 --> 09:20.660
♪ I can't believe
I went and said it ♪

09:20.726 --> 09:25.131
♪ I could run and hide away ♪

09:25.197 --> 09:28.367
♪ Away ♪

09:28.434 --> 09:31.971
- ♪ Piri you don't have to cry ♪

09:32.038 --> 09:36.709
{\an3}♪ The truth is always better
than living a lie ♪

09:36.776 --> 09:39.045
♪ It's okay ♪

09:39.111 --> 09:40.813
{\an3}It's okay.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.782
{\an3}I totally get
what you're saying.

09:42.848 --> 09:45.651
{\an3}Sometimes both my parents
wanna hang out with me,

09:45.718 --> 09:48.354
{\an3}but I just wanna
spend time with Mom

09:48.421 --> 09:50.323
or watch a movie with Dad.

09:50.389 --> 09:52.458
- I guess that's the same thing.

09:52.525 --> 09:54.293
{\an3}- Wanting to spend time alone
with someone

09:54.360 --> 09:56.195
doesn't make you a bad person.

09:56.262 --> 09:57.330
It's normal.

09:57.396 --> 09:58.764
{\an1}- N--nor--

09:58.831 --> 09:59.665
{\an1}norma--

09:59.732 --> 10:03.269
{\an1}norm-al--mal.
Normal.

10:03.336 --> 10:04.570
- Next time,
just tell me

10:04.637 --> 10:06.739
{\an3}instead of trapping us
in a magical garden.

10:06.806 --> 10:08.741
- That seems so simple.

10:08.808 --> 10:10.476
- Hey, I'm free!

10:10.543 --> 10:11.677
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

10:11.744 --> 10:13.479
- Uh, are we cool?

10:13.546 --> 10:15.014
- We're cool.

10:15.081 --> 10:16.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:16.816 --> 10:19.251
both:
♪ Okay lets go! ♪

10:19.318 --> 10:21.387
♪ Kick up our heels! ♪

10:21.454 --> 10:23.556
♪ Let's jump and run ♪

10:23.622 --> 10:26.158
♪ And do cartwheels ♪

10:26.225 --> 10:28.294
♪ It's time to play ♪

10:28.361 --> 10:30.262
♪ Under the sun ♪

10:30.329 --> 10:32.531
♪ We'll be climbing trees ♪

10:32.598 --> 10:35.001
♪ And having fun ♪

10:35.067 --> 10:40.206
♪ And we both know the lyrics
to this song somehow ♪

10:40.272 --> 10:44.410
♪ 'Cause we'll always have
our friendship ♪

10:44.477 --> 10:48.547
♪ The way we do just now ♪

10:51.117 --> 10:53.519
{\an1}- Are you guys sure it's safe
to play here now?

10:53.586 --> 10:56.622
{\an3}- Harvey said Gordon attacked us
before 'cause of feelings,

10:56.689 --> 10:59.258
{\an3}but then I zoned out,
and now we're here.

10:59.325 --> 11:00.626
- Hey, you guys,

11:00.693 --> 11:03.696
{\an1}do you wanna play piñata
with us?

11:03.763 --> 11:05.865
{\an1}- We're kind of
doing our own thing over here.

11:05.931 --> 11:07.400
We'll join you guys later.

11:07.466 --> 11:08.501
- Okay!

11:08.567 --> 11:09.769
- Wait, what?
No!

11:09.835 --> 11:11.670
[sticks whacking]
[grunting]

11:11.737 --> 11:12.838
- Wow, Piri.

11:12.905 --> 11:14.774
{\an1}I never noticed
your aura before.

11:16.742 --> 11:17.676
<i>[playful music]</i>

11:17.743 --> 11:19.678
- [yawns]

11:19.745 --> 11:26.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:27.319 --> 11:28.320
[sighs]

11:28.387 --> 11:30.723
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.790 --> 11:32.925
Whoa.

11:35.561 --> 11:37.363
[sighs]

11:38.798 --> 11:41.434
[both laugh]

11:41.500 --> 11:42.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:42.835 --> 11:44.503
[wind blows]

11:44.570 --> 11:46.906
Huh?
[grunts]

11:48.307 --> 11:50.009
{\an3}[groans]

11:50.076 --> 11:57.016
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:06.826 --> 12:09.462
[thunder rumbles]

12:11.697 --> 12:13.332
[sighs]

12:14.400 --> 12:17.336
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

12:17.403 --> 12:24.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:37.990 --> 12:41.127
<i>[funky soft dramatic music]</i>

12:41.193 --> 12:47.133
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:48.634 --> 12:50.069
all: Wow!
- Really amazing!

12:50.136 --> 12:51.337
- This is awesome.
- This is--

12:51.403 --> 12:52.771
I don't even have words
for this.

12:52.838 --> 12:56.742
- Look.
<i>- I am Johnny Tornado.</i>

12:56.809 --> 12:57.877
[explosion]

12:57.943 --> 12:59.612
<i>My story takes place</i>

12:59.678 --> 13:00.980
<i>in a distant land.</i>

13:01.046 --> 13:03.215
<i>Is it the future?</i>
<i>The past?</i>

13:03.282 --> 13:06.385
<i>Either way,</i>
<i>everything's dirty.</i>

13:09.421 --> 13:12.658
<i>I patrol the wasteland</i>
<i>looking for scrap metal</i>

13:12.725 --> 13:16.495
<i>so that I can finish building</i>
<i>my awesome motorcycle,</i>

13:16.562 --> 13:17.963
<i>but wait...</i>

13:18.030 --> 13:20.032
<i>danger is close.</i>

13:20.099 --> 13:23.302
<i>A mighty creature threatens</i>
<i>to attack two drifters.</i>

13:23.369 --> 13:26.038
- We're tough,
but we need to be tougher

13:26.105 --> 13:28.374
because this monster
is super tough.

13:28.440 --> 13:32.044
{\an3}- Whoa, for some reason,
I really like that character.

13:32.111 --> 13:33.846
- I must protect them.

13:33.913 --> 13:36.115
<i>Johnny Tornado</i>
<i>runs to the rescue.</i>

13:36.182 --> 13:38.651
<i>- But will he</i>
<i>and his new friends survive?</i>

13:38.717 --> 13:40.452
- [growling]
<i>- Survive!</i>

13:40.519 --> 13:42.788
<i>Well, you're gonna have</i>
<i>to wait and see</i>

13:42.855 --> 13:44.857
<i>'cause,</i>
<i>um, the stories not over.</i>

13:44.924 --> 13:46.225
{\an1}<i>It's...</i>

13:47.459 --> 13:49.862
all: Whoa!

13:49.929 --> 13:51.363
- How did this get made?

13:51.430 --> 13:54.066
{\an1}Like, what type of machine
made this?

13:54.133 --> 13:56.835
{\an3}- Rooter, it was created
by an artist.

13:56.902 --> 13:58.837
- No, no, that can't be right.

13:58.904 --> 14:01.240
- Yeah, but who is this artist?

14:01.307 --> 14:04.577
{\an1}They literally
left us zero clues.

14:04.643 --> 14:06.111
- Hey, has anyone seen Kratz?

14:06.178 --> 14:09.014
{\an3}- Stop wasting time asking
random, pointless questions.

14:09.081 --> 14:11.317
{\an3}We're trying to figure out
who drew the comic.

14:11.383 --> 14:14.420
{\an3}- Well, whoever they are,
they're awesome.

14:14.486 --> 14:17.156
{\an3}- Whom.
It's whomever they are, Foo.

14:17.223 --> 14:19.558
{\an3}Whomever they are,
they're awesome.

14:19.625 --> 14:20.993
- Thank you, Harvey.

14:21.060 --> 14:24.196
<i>[exciting music]</i>

14:24.263 --> 14:27.600
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:27.666 --> 14:31.203
{\an1}- Thank you, all, for joining
my monster-fighting team.

14:31.270 --> 14:34.673
Now, let's kick some tail.

14:34.740 --> 14:41.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:42.448 --> 14:43.616
- A new comic!

14:43.682 --> 14:45.884
[all talking at once]
- It's amazing!

14:45.951 --> 14:47.386
- Amazing!

14:47.453 --> 14:48.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:48.721 --> 14:50.089
{\an3}- I'm beginning
to really like you,

14:50.155 --> 14:52.458
{\an3}Commander Rocket.
Do you like me?

14:52.524 --> 14:55.261
- I do, but only as friends.

14:55.327 --> 14:57.863
- Cool, that's totally fine,
and it doesn't hurt my heart.

14:57.930 --> 14:59.798
- Hang in there, Johnny.

14:59.865 --> 15:01.734
[both grunting]

15:01.800 --> 15:04.470
- Johnny Tornado's got something
for everyone.

15:04.536 --> 15:06.805
- I like the guy
with the trident.

15:06.872 --> 15:08.540
- I came here to do two things:

15:08.607 --> 15:11.277
Kiss my parents
and throw my trident.

15:11.343 --> 15:14.013
And I've already
kissed my parents.

15:14.079 --> 15:17.249
[grunts]
- [snarling]

15:17.316 --> 15:19.652
- Ah.
all: Wow.

15:19.718 --> 15:22.588
- Look out, team.
Everything's about to explode

15:22.655 --> 15:23.756
for no reason.

15:23.822 --> 15:25.024
[explosion]

15:25.090 --> 15:27.760
[pencil scratching]

15:27.826 --> 15:29.695
[doorbell rings]

15:29.762 --> 15:31.430
- Is that my doorbell?

15:31.497 --> 15:34.199
I've never actually
heard it ring.

15:34.266 --> 15:36.101
Ah!
- Hi, Kratz.

15:36.168 --> 15:38.771
- Wh--what're you doing here?

15:38.837 --> 15:40.105
- Well, I found some stuff

15:40.172 --> 15:42.141
{\an3}over by the newest
"Johnny Tornado" comic

15:42.207 --> 15:43.842
{\an3}that I think
might belong to you.

15:43.909 --> 15:45.311
{\an1}- Uh...

15:45.377 --> 15:47.479
{\an3}- I found your ink-stained
library card,

15:47.546 --> 15:49.848
{\an3}an assortment
of pens and pencils,

15:49.915 --> 15:52.985
{\an3}and an inappropriate
science book.

15:53.052 --> 15:55.120
- Um, well, I can explain.

15:55.187 --> 15:57.389
{\an1}- Hey, what if that
mystery artist

15:57.456 --> 16:01.093
is someone we know.
- Hmm, I wonder.

16:01.160 --> 16:02.561
- Yo, Kratz!
- Hi, Kratz!

16:02.628 --> 16:04.563
- Hey, gu--ah!

16:04.630 --> 16:06.565
- Whoops, sorry!

16:06.632 --> 16:09.635
- Harvey, a word?

16:09.702 --> 16:11.804
I need to tell you something.

16:11.870 --> 16:13.238
Can you keep a secret?

16:13.305 --> 16:15.774
{\an3}- I got a few
I'm taking to the grave.

16:15.841 --> 16:17.876
- Good 'cause I'm--

16:17.943 --> 16:20.446
{\an1}I'm the artist
behind "Johnny Tornado."

16:20.512 --> 16:23.882
{\an3}- Wha?
Kratz, that's so cool!

16:23.949 --> 16:27.052
{\an3}Oh, my gosh.
You gotta tell everyone!

16:27.119 --> 16:29.722
{\an1}- No way, Harvey.
Don't you see?

16:29.788 --> 16:33.392
{\an1}If people know I did it,
they won't like it anymore.

16:33.459 --> 16:34.593
{\an1}I stink.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.862
{\an3}- You're being too hard
on yourself.

16:36.929 --> 16:38.530
What if I told them for you?

16:38.597 --> 16:39.865
- Harvey, no!

16:39.932 --> 16:41.333
{\an1}Ah!
[grunts]

16:41.400 --> 16:43.602
Please don't tell anyone.

16:43.669 --> 16:45.804
{\an3}- What if I just told
one person?

16:45.871 --> 16:47.606
- How about no persons.

16:47.673 --> 16:49.341
Please, Harvey.

16:49.408 --> 16:50.876
{\an1}Please?

16:50.943 --> 16:54.012
Promise you won't tell anyone.

16:54.079 --> 16:55.714
{\an3}- Okay.

16:55.781 --> 16:57.683
- Oh, my gosh, it's so cool!
- What is that?

16:57.750 --> 16:59.618
[all talking at once]

16:59.685 --> 17:01.787
{\an1}- Mystery solved.
Who would have thought?

17:01.854 --> 17:04.323
- What's going on?
- Didn't you guys hear?

17:04.390 --> 17:06.425
We found out who drew the comic.

17:06.492 --> 17:07.760
- Yo--you did?

17:07.826 --> 17:09.395
- Yeah!
It was...

17:09.461 --> 17:10.963
Princess!

17:11.029 --> 17:12.897
- There.
- Wow.

17:12.964 --> 17:14.165
both: Princess?

17:14.233 --> 17:16.335
{\an1}- You have to tell me
what pens you use.

17:16.402 --> 17:18.436
{\an3}- Did you really
draw those freehand?

17:18.503 --> 17:21.073
- Princess is like a celebrity!
- Yeah.

17:21.140 --> 17:22.741
{\an3}Who knew she was good
at anything.

17:22.808 --> 17:24.810
- I love Johnny Tornado!

17:24.877 --> 17:26.145
- Ew, who the heck's that?

17:26.211 --> 17:27.546
Tell me I'm great.

17:27.613 --> 17:30.082
- How can she take credit
like that?

17:30.149 --> 17:31.550
This is an outrage!

17:31.617 --> 17:34.353
{\an1}- [sighs] I guess
this was bound to happen.

17:34.420 --> 17:38.157
{\an3}- Hey, mister, bag up that
bad attitude and throw it away!

17:38.223 --> 17:41.093
{\an3}This is your chance.
You gotta say something!

17:41.160 --> 17:43.095
{\an1}- No, no, no.
I can't!

17:43.162 --> 17:45.998
{\an1}- Hey, guys,
I have an announcement to make!

17:46.064 --> 17:48.133
- No, you promised.

17:48.200 --> 17:49.701
- What is it, Harvey?

17:49.768 --> 17:51.970
- Uh, I just wanted to say,

17:52.037 --> 17:54.840
{\an3}uh...
[sighs]

17:54.907 --> 17:56.742
I think reading is really fun.

17:56.809 --> 17:59.611
- Ugh, why do we even
let him speak?

17:59.678 --> 18:01.713
{\an1}- [sighs]

18:03.048 --> 18:05.984
<i>[soft music]</i>

18:06.051 --> 18:07.586
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:07.653 --> 18:09.321
Oh, Johnny Tornado,

18:09.388 --> 18:11.023
you'd know what to do.

18:11.089 --> 18:13.158
- You're darn right I do.

18:13.225 --> 18:14.960
I know what to do

18:15.027 --> 18:16.428
and so do you.

18:16.495 --> 18:18.797
- Wha?
- Listen to me, Kratz.

18:18.864 --> 18:22.367
I may be super heroic
and crazy strong,

18:22.434 --> 18:25.370
but without you,
I'm nothing.

18:25.437 --> 18:27.506
Take a look in the mirror.

18:27.573 --> 18:29.041
You are Kratz,

18:29.107 --> 18:31.143
creator of "Johnny Tornado,"

18:31.210 --> 18:33.445
and that makes you a hero too.

18:33.512 --> 18:36.982
Now, how are you gonna
fix this problem?

18:37.049 --> 18:39.985
<i>[exciting music]</i>

18:40.052 --> 18:41.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:42.054 --> 18:45.524
[all talking at once]

18:45.591 --> 18:47.693
- Hey, it is I,

18:47.759 --> 18:50.295
{\an1}the real comic--
[grunts]

18:50.362 --> 18:52.698
Anyway, as I was saying,

18:52.764 --> 18:55.968
I am the true artist
of "Johnny Tornado,"

18:56.034 --> 18:59.004
{\an1}and you'll never
figure out who I am

18:59.071 --> 19:00.772
so don't even try.

19:00.839 --> 19:02.474
{\an3}- Oh, let's just
figure out who's not here.

19:02.541 --> 19:04.109
Piri, Claire...
- Present.

19:04.176 --> 19:06.211
- No one knows.
Don't even try.

19:06.278 --> 19:09.515
- I challenge you to an art-off.

19:09.581 --> 19:10.482
[all gasp]

19:10.549 --> 19:14.119
- Whatever, let's do this.

19:14.186 --> 19:15.387
- All right, you two,

19:15.454 --> 19:17.656
I want a good,
clean drawing contest.

19:17.723 --> 19:20.192
No pencil jabs
below the waistband

19:20.259 --> 19:23.061
and keep your eraser shavings
to yourself.

19:23.128 --> 19:25.197
On your marks...
- [growls]

19:25.264 --> 19:27.032
- Get set...

19:27.099 --> 19:28.267
draw!

19:28.333 --> 19:31.470
[cheering]

19:31.537 --> 19:32.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:32.604 --> 19:34.606
- [grunting]

19:34.673 --> 19:35.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:35.474 --> 19:36.975
- Hey, Mr. Mystery.

19:37.042 --> 19:38.243
How's it going?

19:38.310 --> 19:41.780
Oh, man, that is,
like, super great.

19:41.847 --> 19:45.183
{\an1}All right, let's see
what you're up to, Princess.

19:45.250 --> 19:46.652
{\an3}Uh, ugh.

19:46.718 --> 19:49.454
{\an1}Okay, definitely doesn't
look as good as,

19:49.521 --> 19:51.056
{\an1}uh, mystery boy's stuff
over there

19:51.123 --> 19:52.758
{\an1}[shouts]

19:52.824 --> 19:55.093
- [grunting]

19:55.160 --> 19:56.461
- Not cool, Princess!

19:56.528 --> 19:58.864
You know how I feel
about pencil jabs.

19:58.931 --> 20:00.198
{\an3}- Fine.

20:00.265 --> 20:03.402
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:03.468 --> 20:05.470
[cheers and laughter]

20:05.537 --> 20:07.839
- Good job,
monster-fighting team.

20:07.906 --> 20:11.376
We fought all the monsters
as a team.

20:11.443 --> 20:13.412
all: Yay!
- That's right team, we did!

20:13.478 --> 20:15.948
- This is some primo stuff.

20:16.014 --> 20:18.550
- [grunts]
[cheers]

20:18.617 --> 20:21.086
- Hey, everyone, I'm stupid!

20:21.153 --> 20:23.088
- I'm stupid too!

20:23.155 --> 20:24.389
[together] We're all stupid!

20:24.456 --> 20:25.857
We're all stupid!
- I'm so stupid!

20:25.924 --> 20:27.125
all: I'm so stupid!

20:27.192 --> 20:28.493
La, la, la, la, la!

20:28.560 --> 20:32.564
- Hey, who is
that beautiful girl over there?

20:32.631 --> 20:35.801
- My name is
Gorgeous Awesome-Muscles.

20:35.867 --> 20:37.603
Now who wants
to clean the crumbs

20:37.669 --> 20:38.971
out of my toes?

20:39.037 --> 20:40.238
{\an1}- Ooh, me!
Please, I wanna do it!

20:40.305 --> 20:42.507
- Princess, I wanna do it!
- Me!

20:42.574 --> 20:44.843
- I don't know.
Princess's comic

20:44.910 --> 20:47.579
just doesn't seem as good
as her earlier work.

20:47.646 --> 20:51.516
- Unless, Princess is lying
about being the real artist.

20:51.583 --> 20:53.285
- Has she ever lied before?

20:53.352 --> 20:54.620
- Yeah, quite a bit.

20:54.686 --> 20:57.522
{\an1}- Let's compare hers
with the mystery artist.

20:57.589 --> 20:59.891
[all talking at once]

20:59.958 --> 21:02.628
- [grunting]

21:02.694 --> 21:03.895
{\an3}You!

21:03.962 --> 21:06.632
{\an3}Time to figure out
who the heck you are!

21:06.698 --> 21:07.933
- No, no, wait.

21:08.000 --> 21:09.434
- Princess,
this is very unsportsmanlike!

21:09.501 --> 21:11.737
- No, no!
- [grunts]

21:11.803 --> 21:12.971
[all gasp]

21:13.038 --> 21:14.973
{\an3}- Ew, what the--
ugh, really?

21:15.040 --> 21:17.242
- It was Kratz?
- Oh, I can't believe this.

21:17.309 --> 21:18.844
[all talking at once]

21:18.910 --> 21:20.912
- It turns out,
it's stupid Kratz.

21:20.979 --> 21:23.315
{\an3}What do you think
of your mystery artist now?

21:23.382 --> 21:25.350
{\an1}- Oh, man.

21:25.417 --> 21:27.986
[all cheering]

21:29.187 --> 21:30.922
- Your comic's awesome, Kratz!

21:30.989 --> 21:32.257
- You the man!

21:32.324 --> 21:34.660
all: [cheering and chanting]
Kratz!

21:34.726 --> 21:37.629
{\an3}- What?
Nothing makes sense anymore!

21:37.696 --> 21:41.400
{\an3}[grunts]
My body is shutting down.

21:41.466 --> 21:43.268
<i>[victorious music]</i>

21:43.335 --> 21:45.470
- Wh--whoa!

21:47.439 --> 21:49.541
- Kratz, please sign my comic.

21:49.608 --> 21:51.977
- Kratz, your my inspiration.

21:52.044 --> 21:53.478
- Do a little signature on it.

21:53.545 --> 21:54.880
[laughing]
Come on, I love you.

21:54.946 --> 21:57.783
- Aw, yeah, Kratz.
Sign my comic, man!

21:57.849 --> 21:59.851
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:01.987 --> 22:04.923
{\an8}<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.990 --> 22:11.930
{\an7}<i>♪ ♪</i>
